## Add Annotations

The original R example also shows `I()` for placing annotations with relative coordinates inside the plotting area.
There does not appear to be a direct `I()` equivalent for `annotate()` in plotnine, so these examples use data coordinates.

::: {#80fc6502 .cell execution_count=30}
``` {.python .cell-code}
(
    organdata
    .ggplot(aes(x = "roads", y = "donors"))
